Certainly, here are several example sentences in Serbian that use the word "predaj" in different forms and positions, with the starred word indicated with an asterisk (*) and the English translations provided in parentheses:

1. *Predaj* mi tu knjigu. (Give me that book.)
2. Želim da se *predam* policiji. (I want to surrender to the police.)
3. Oni su nam *predali* izveštaj na vreme. (They submitted the report to us on time.)
4. Učitelj je *predao* čas istorije. (The teacher taught the history class.)
5. Molim vas, *predajte* svoje karte za bioskop. (Please hand over your cinema tickets.)
6. Ko će biti *predavač* na konferenciji? (Who will be the lecturer at the conference?)
7. *Predajem* se - ne mogu dalje. (I give up - I can't go on.)
8. Rekao sam mu da *preda* poruku. (I told him to deliver the message.)
9. Ona će *predavati* engleski u novoj školi. (She will teach English at the new school.)
10. Sutradan sam *predao* zahtev za vizu. (The next day, I submitted my visa application.)

I hope these sentences help illustrate the various ways in which the word "predaj" can be used in Serbian!